{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"body":"2nd plan-review PASS (signed, file-impact now pass). Triage of new findings: (a) VALID — materialize_tickets() in src/rebar/_snapshot/repo_snapshot.py is a genuine 5th site (pins origin/tickets for the code-reading gates). Including it via a default-preserving remote='origin' param on resolve_ref/_fetch_origin/_has_remote so the security-sensitive CODE snapshot path (origin/main) is byte-for-byte unchanged and only the tickets path uses the configured remote. (b) DISMISSED as hallucinated — 'review_bot/config.py already has tickets_remote/TICKETS_REMOTE': grep -rniE 'tickets_remote|TICKETS_REMOTE' src/rebar returns ZERO hits. (c) DISMISSED — 'CLAUDE.md has no git-workflow section': it has '## Git workflow (code changes)' (matched loosely by the reviewer's literal 'git-workflow' grep)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783038051267189001,"uuid":"ef582e7b-59eb-462f-905a-286cd885c0f3"}